Selected Answer: B
I think the correct answer is 3. I tested in an org.
The explanation:
 - starting with count=0;
 - According the order of execution, before triggers are the first to run, so count = 1;
 - Workflow are the next execution to run, so count = 2;
- but, when evaluting workflows, the triggers are executed again, so count = 3;
 - the execution finishes once there is no more to do and the re-evaluate workflow is not checked.

so the count will be 3

